            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Contains anti-Castro letters by Cuban residents, solicited for a never-published supplement to the 
                <emph render="italic">New Leader</emph>.</abstract>
            <physdesc id="ref1" label="General Physical Description note">5 linear inches (1 box)</physdesc>
        </did>
        <acqinfo id="ref4">
            <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
            <p>Gift of the 
                <emph render="italic">New Leader</emph> in 1963. The accession number 1963.023 is associated with this gift.</p>
        </acqinfo>
        <accessrestrict id="ref5">
            <head>Access Restrictions</head>
            <p>Open for research without restrictions.</p>
        </accessrestrict>
        <bioghist id="ref8">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Norman Jacobs of the 
                <emph render="italic">New Leader</emph>, a liberal anti-communist periodical, solicited letters from Cubans for a special supplement on Cuba under Castro, that was never published.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref9">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The collection contains approximately 100 letters by Cuban residents to United States relatives and friends describing conditions in Cuba. The letters, all anti-Castro, describe every-day life, the fates of acquaintances, objections to the regime and provide contemporary anti-Castro jokes and rumors. The collection includes the original letters as well as English translations.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement id="ref10">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>Within each series the folders are arranged alphabetically and numerically.</p>
            <p>the collection is organized into two series:</p>
            <list type="ordered">
                <item>1.Originals</item>
                <item>2. Translations.</item>
            </list>
        </arrangement>
        <userestrict id="ref27">
            <head>Use Restrictions</head>
            <p>The Tamiment Library does not have information about who owns copyright to this collection. Materials in this collection are expected to enter the public domain in 2083. The Tamiment Library is not authorized to grant permission to publish or reproduce materials in this collection.</p>
        </userestrict>
